Class Prim<V,X extends Comparable<X> & Sequenced>

Direct Known Subclasses:
GeoPrim
public class Prim<V,X extends Comparable<X> & Sequenced> extends MST<V,X> implements Iterable<Edge<V,X>>
The Prim class represents a solution to the Minimum Spanning Tree (MST) problem using Prim's algorithm. It extends the MST abstract class and provides an implementation for finding the MST for a given edge-weighted graph. This class uses a lazy approach where edges are processed incrementally during the traversal of the graph.

    • getMST

      public EdgeGraph<V,X> getMST()
      Generates and returns the Minimum Spanning Tree (MST) for the edge-weighted graph. Each edge in the MST is assigned a unique sequence number based on its order of inclusion.
